entries.title: Tear gas and fireworks as pension protests turn violent in Paris
entries.description: French demonstrations against President Macron’s plan to raise the retirement age stayed mostly peaceful but clashes broke out in Paris, with police using tear gas and protesters throwing fireworks and other missiles.

entries.description: Two Iranian-born Swedish brothers were given lengthy prison sentences on Thursday for spying for Russia and its military intelligence service GRU for a decade

entries.title: In Peru, protesters pour from remote Andean regions, demand president resign
entries.description: People poured into Peru’s capital, many from remote Andean regions, for a protest against Pres.  Dina Boluarte and in support of ousted president Pedro Castillo.

entries.title: Lula: Brazil's intelligence services failed ahead of Brasilia pro-Bolsonaro riots
entries.description: Brazilian President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva said his intelligence services failed when Brasilia buildings were stormed by supporters of former Pres. Bolsonaro.

entries.title: Ukrainian authorities begin investigating deadly helicopter crash
entries.description: Ukrainian authorities are working to pick up the pieces of yesterday’s deadly helicopter crash as investigators begin looking into what could have caused the chopper to fall near a kindergarten in a Kyiv suburb. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez reports from Brovary, Ukraine.

entries.title: Top Israeli legal official tells Netanyahu to fire key ally after Supreme Court ruling
entries.description: Israel’s attorney general has told Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu he must fire a key Cabinet ally,  following a Supreme Court ruling that disqualified him.

entries.title: Wintry weather leaves 78 dead in Afghanistan, Taliban says
entries.description: Taliban officials said Thursday that 78 people have died in just over a week during the harsh winter in Afghanistan, deepening the country’s humanitarian

entries.title: Nationwide strike in France against Macron’s plan to raise retirement age
entries.description: Workers in many French cities took to the streets Thursday to reject proposed pension changes that would push back the retirement age.

entries.title: Chinese hospitals creak under the strain of a huge Covid outbreak
entries.description: A Covid-19 outbreak in China following the sudden end of “zero-Covid” rules has brought chaotic scenes in overcrowded hospitals in Shanghai.

entries.title: At least 4 U.S. residents among those killed in Nepal plane crash
entries.description: Two Americans and two permanent residents living in the United States were among the 72 people killed after a plane crashed in Nepal over the weekend.

entries.title: New Zealanders shocked by Ardern's resignation announcement
entries.description: There was widespread surprise that New Zealand's Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern intends to step down.

entries.title: France hit by nationwide strike as unions fight Macron’s plan to raise retirement age
entries.description: French workers angry over proposed changes to retirement rules launched nationwide strikes and protests Thursday seen as a major test for Emmanuel Macron.

entries.title: Russia opens espionage case against U.S. citizen
entries.description: Russia has opened a criminal case against a United States citizen on suspicion of espionage, the country's Federal Security Service announced Thursday.

entries.title: ‘For me it’s time’: Jacinda Ardern steps down as New Zealand's Prime Minister
entries.description: Jacinda Ardern held a press conference where she announced her resignation as New Zealand's Prime Minister, and said she will not be seeking re-election. She said that after holding the position for 5 and a half years, she no longer "has enough in the tank" to do the job justice.

entries.title: Ukrainian soldiers get prosthetic limbs from Maryland medical center
entries.description: Russia’s war in Ukraine has taken a devastating toll on soldiers, some of whom have lost limbs to blast injuries. One medical center in Maryland is creating prosthetic limbs for Ukrainian soldiers and teaching them how to use them. NBC News’ Aaron Gilchrist shares more details.

entries.title: Helicopter crash in Ukraine kills 14 including top government official
entries.description: A helicopter crash in Ukraine killed 14 people, including Ukraine’s interior minister who was responsible for the country’s internal security. NBC News’ Raf Sanchez has more details on President Zelenskyy’s response.
